⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Sheep
node AFM · AFM · ⟦The Sheep:AFM:4262ea⟧

WHO   — The Sheep — the chanting masses
WHAT  — The slogan-trained masses: deployed to shout down any dangerous question at exactly the right moment.
WHERE — AFM · ANIMAL FARM  Framework inputs: Animal Farm (George Orwell, 1945)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because a population that chants cannot be reasoned with — the sheep are how the regime kills an argument before it forms.
HOW   — By a memorised slogan, bleated on cue, amended overnight when the Party's line reverses.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Four legs good, two legs bad — and when they needed it, two legs BETTER; I never knew the difference, and that was exactly my use.

